Privacy Policy

Effective date: July 2026

IO HELPER Privacy Policy

IO HELPER is an extension developed exclusively for moderators of the CYBERSHOKE project.

We respect your privacy and are committed to being transparent about how the extension works.

Data Collection

IO HELPER does not collect, store, transmit, sell, or share any personal information.

The extension does not collect:

Personal information
Email addresses
Passwords
Cookies
Browsing history
Financial information
Location data
Analytics or tracking data
Data Processing

The extension processes information available on the CYBERSHOKE moderation website locally within your browser to provide its functionality, including:

Analyzing chat history for moderation assistance.
Highlighting complaint triggers.
Translating chat messages.
Displaying moderator information.
Automatically filling moderation templates.
Managing interface elements.
Detecting duplicate server reports.

This processing happens entirely on the user's device.

Local Storage

IO HELPER stores only extension settings and cached configuration data using the browser's local storage.

Examples include:

User preferences.
Feature settings.
Cached moderation configuration downloaded from the official GitHub repository.

This data never leaves your browser.

Network Requests

The extension may connect to:

The official CYBERSHOKE moderation website.
The official GitHub repository to download the latest configuration file.
Translation services when the translation feature is enabled.

These requests are required solely for the extension's functionality.

Third-Party Services

When the translation feature is enabled, translated text may be processed by a third-party translation service.

No additional personal information is intentionally transmitted.

Data Sharing

IO HELPER does not sell, rent, or share user data with third parties.

Changes

This Privacy Policy may be updated when new features are added.

Contact

If you have any questions regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact the extension developer through the official CYBERSHOKE project or the project's GitHub repository.